K2IA BRIEF INTRODUCTION TO SANDERS JOHNSON SMITH LTDMJ
 
 
IK2INTRODUCTIONMJ
 
The firm was founded in April 1974 by Don M.  Sanders, Ross  N.   Johnson  and
John  S.   Smith,  who had worked together previously over a period of several
years, and prior to forming the company were a Partner, Associate  and  Senior
Engineer in another consulting engineering practice.
 
In 1978, Don Sanders retired from active participation and withdrew fully from
the Company in 1981.
 
In late 1981 the Company appointed as a Director Tiit (Ted) Raba, one  of  the
foundation  staff  members,  who  worked  continuously  with  the  firm in the
intervening years.
 
In April 1983, Graham G.  Cook joined the firm as a Director.  Graham Cook had
previously been an Associate in an electrical engineering consulting practice.
 
The Principals and  staff  of  the  firm  are  experienced  in  the  areas  of
Mechanical  and  Electrical  Building  Services  and Industrial Services, with
special  experience  in  Institutional  Laundries,  Electric  and   Electronic
Control,   Automation   and   Computer   Control   Techniques,  Microprocessor
Applications and Software Review, Energy Utilisation,  Electricity  Generation
and Resource Conservation.
 
The firm does  not  carry  out  work  in  civil  and  structural  engineering,
surveying  or  architecture.  When required, the firm works closely with other
consultants in those fields, in either primary or secondary  consultant  role,
to   produce   co-ordinated  designs.   In  addition  to  commissions  in  the
traditional role of consultant to the owner or architect, the firm  also  acts
as  technical  advisor  to  contractors  undertaking  "design  and build" type
projects, in both the building services and industrial engineering fields.
 
The firm is based in Wellington but the Principals and staff regularly  travel
throughout the country and overseas as required.
 






















                                      - 1 -

 
 
 
IK2FIELDS OF WORKMJ
 
 
A more detailed list of fields of work carried out by the firm is as follows :
 
     1.  Mechanical  services  for  buildings,  ranging  from  simple  heating
         systems,  to  full  comfort  or  process air-conditioning systems and
         total or selective energy systems.
 
     2.  All electrical building services.
 
     3.  Specialised lighting systems  for  aesthetic,  technical  or  outdoor
         purposes including road lighting.
 
     4.  Plumbing, drainage and water services (hydraulic  services),  to  all
         types of buildings.
 
     5.  Fire protection and security systems including automatic  sprinklers,
         thermal and ionisation detector systems etc.
 
     6.  Lift and escalator services including traffic analyses.
 
     7.  Electrical,   electronic   and   pneumatic   control   systems    for
         environmental  control  including  computer  based   building  energy
         management systems.
 
     8.  Automation and  process  control  and  monitoring  systems  based  on
         pneumatic  or electrical analogue and digital (PLC, microprocessor or
         computer) techniques.
 
     9. Standby  and  base-load  power  generation  systems  including   high
         voltage.
 
     10. Boilerplant, both steam and hot water,  using  all  available  fuels,
         including coal, gas, woodwaste and refuse.
 
     11. Laundry design,  with  emphasis  on  hospital  and  commercial  linen
         service applications, including selection of processes and machinery,
         flow  patterns  and  equipment  layout,  together   with   associated
         mechanical, electrical and plumbing services.
 
     12. Swimming pool  design  services  for  filtration,  heating,  chemical
         dosing, lighting, ventilation and associated systems.
 
     13. System  analysis  and  problem  solving  in  power   generation   and
         distribution and in process controls.
 
     14. Process refrigeration and cooling applications.
 
     15. Energy conservation studies and audits.






                                      - 2 -

 
 
 
     16. Plant  and  Machinery  valuations  for  insurance   and   replacement
         purposes.
 
     17. Engineering accident investigations.
 
     18. Expert witness services in litigation.
 
 
 
In each of the fields mentioned, the firm can provide a variety  of  services,
to meet the needs of individual clients.  These range from feasibility studies
and design reports, to full design and management of  a  project  from  sketch
plan   design,  preparation  of  full  working  drawings  and  specifications,
schedules of quantities, calling tenders, awarding contracts, supervision  and
administration   of   the   contract   and   commissioning  of  the  completed
installation.
 







































                                      - 3 -

 
 
 
IK2SCHEDULES OF QUANTITIESMJ
 
While the firm does not provide quantity surveying  services  on  an  external
consulting  basis,  it  does carry out measurement and preparation of quantity
schedules for projects designed by the firm.  Such schedules are  prepared  by
experienced  staff  members  other than those involved in the actual design of
the project, to provide an independent checking procedure on  the  design  and
documentation  in addition to compiling the schedule.  Because the schedule is
prepared by engineers or technicians fully experienced in the  design  of  the
services  and in the relevant trade practices, it becomes a more useful, hence
more valuable document in the hands of the tenderer and subsequent contractor.
 
 
IK2AFFILIATIONSMJ
 
The Principals of the firm  are  Members  of  the  Association  of  Consulting
Engineers  of  New Zealand, and the activities of the firm are governed by the
Rules of that association and  the  Code  of  Ethics  of  the  Institution  of
Professional Engineers of New Zealand.
 
The  Principals,  senior   Associates,   and   several   staff   members   are
professionally   qualified,   most  being  at  least  New  Zealand  Registered
Engineers.
 
Unless specially negotiated,  all  commissions  undertaken  by  the  firm  are
accepted  in  accordance with the Institution of Professional Engineers of New
Zealand Conditions of Engagement and Scales of  Minimum  Fees  for  Consulting
Engineers, as currently in force.
 
For the purposes of administration only, the firm is incorporated as a Limited
Company, with appropriate capital structure and shareholding.  In this regard,
the limitations imposed by the Rules of Association of Consulting Engineers of
New  Zealand  are  fully  complied with, and the relevant details will be made
available to prospective Clients upon request.
 
 
IK2COMPUTER FACILITIESMJ
 
The firm operates its own Digital Equipment Corporation PDP  11/04  and  11/40
computers  with a total of 60 MB of disc drives, letter quality and dot matrix
printers and special interfaces with  supporting  software  for  carrying  out
engineering   calculations,  word  processing  and  accounting  functions  and
cross-assembly and testing of microprocessor program memory.
 
The services of the computers and the firm's in-house programming capabilities
are  available  to  Clients  on  a leased-time basis in addition to the normal
computing work carried out as part of our engineering design commissions.









